title: For Sale:  Yugo K98 Mauser
postcontent: For sale here is a really nice 8MM Yugoslavian K98 mauser capture rifle. In the second world war, the Yugoslavians converted many of the weapons they confiscated from the Germans to use for themselves. Because of this, the German markings were scrubbed and replaced with the Yugo Crest. The only difference between the German and Yugo K98s is the markings, so really it is a German K98 with a Yugo Crest.The weapon is in excellent condition. The stock has minor indentations from clear use, but overall is very good looking to me. The bore is bright, sharp, and tight at the muzzle. The action is smooth as with most Mauser rifles. Comes with the attached sling.For this rifle I am asking $450 OBO. This is a great deal on a rifle that is rapidly becoming more and more scarce.
